(The software described here addresses that gap for a bounded research-software use case. It) Tj
0 -14 Td
(converts OpenTelemetry Protocol \(OTLP\) JSON trace data into an Execution Evidence and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Operation Accountability Profile \(EEOAP\) evidence object. In this repository, EEOAP is a) Tj
0 -14 Td
(versioned, repository-scoped JSON schema and validation target, documented in) Tj
0 -14 Td
(`docs/public/EEOAP_v0.1_public_spec.md` and `specs/eeoap/v0.1/eeoap.schema.json`. This) Tj
0 -14 Td
(implementation shows how OpenTelemetry trace data can be transformed into an Execution) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Evidence and Operation Accountability Profile record with preserved identifiers, provenance) Tj
0 -14 Td
(links, and validator-readable output. The artifact complements OpenTelemetry by targeting) Tj
0 -14 Td
(validator-readable execution evidence rather than telemetry capture.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(The intended users are researchers, tool builders, and developers who already have) Tj
0 -14 Td
(OpenTelemetry trace exports and want to inspect how a run can be represented as structured) Tj
0 -14 Td
(execution evidence. The artifact is useful when the question is not only "what spans were) Tj
0 -14 Td
(observed?" but also "which trace produced this evidence object, what identifiers and digests) Tj
0 -14 Td
(were preserved, and did the generated object pass the repository validator?") Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
